UK PM - Wirral loss won ' t alter election date . British Prime Minister John Major said on Friday that his party ' s defeat in the Wirral by - election would not alter his preferred date for a general election . " I don ' t believe last night ' s by - election result , although it puts us in a minority of one , will alter the date I have in mind for the election , " Major said in a broadcast interview during a visit to Scotland . Major refused to say if May 1 was his top choice , as is widely believed , but predicted the Conservatives would win . On Thursday , Labour candidate Ben Chapman overturned a Conservative majority of 8 , 183 votes to win the affluent northwestern constituency of Wirral South by a margin of 7 , 888 votes . Major vowed to recapture the seat at the general election , which must be held by May 22 . 
